## Verification gate (required)

Before opening a pull request, call the `merge-gate` MCP tool **`evaluate_diff`** with the
task description (and `base_ref` if the base branch isn't `origin/main`).

- If `verdict` is `"fail"`, fix every `blocker` violation and call `evaluate_diff` again.
  Repeat until `verdict` is `"pass"`.
- Treat `warn` violations as review notes: address them or justify them in the PR body.
- Paste the final `Verdict` JSON into the PR body as evidence.

The gate runs targeted tests and a rubric judge over your branch diff. Every violation
cites a real `file:line` from the diff — if it doesn't point at your change, it was dropped.
